    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen opening a manpage inside Neovim using `:Man` with environment variable `MANPAGER=\"nvim +Man!\"`, it hangs for a while and then shows this error:\n```\nman.lua: /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:749: /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:740: BufReadCmd Autocommands for \"man://*\": Vim(append):Lua callback: /usr/local/sh are/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:25: attempt to index local 'r' (a nil value)\nstack traceback:\n        /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:25: in function 'system'\n        /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:431: in function 'get_page'\n        /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:770: in function 'read_page'\n        /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/man.lua:34: in function </usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/man.lua:33>\n        [C]: in function 'stag'\n        /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:740: in function </usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:734>\n        [C]: in function 'pcall'\n        /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:734: in function </usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/man.lua:695>\n        [C]: in function 'pcall'\n        /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/man.lua:11: in function </usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/man.lua:6>\n```\n\nI think the reason is a call to `vim.system` for `man -l <path>` in `runtime/lua/man.lua` with `MANPAGER` being Neovim. I'll try to submit a PR fix soon :)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nMANPAGER=\"nvim +Man!\" nvim --clean\n:Man man(1)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n*opens the `man(1)` manpage buffer*\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-41074421 Build type: Debug LuaJIT 2.1.1744317938\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo `:Man` on vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFreeBSD 16.0-CURRENT\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20250730-110715-6a493f88\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
